 treatment as well.

22
00:01:23,120 --> 00:01:27,840
 Some advanced plans may even cover IVF treatments, serogasy or stem cell preservation.

23
00:01:28,000 --> 00:01:30,240
 But folks, there are limitations.

24
00:01:30,240 --> 00:01:31,880
 Waiting period is the first one.

25
00:01:31,880 --> 00:01:35,840
 Most plans have a two to four year wait before you can claim maternity.

26
00:01:35,840 --> 00:01:37,360
 There is also sublimit.

27
00:01:37,360 --> 00:01:41,560
 Many policies cap the claim amount, for example, 50,000 or one lakh rupee max.

28
00:01:41,560 --> 00:01:44,560
 There's also something called as dual spouse condition.

29
00:01:44,560 --> 00:01:45,600
 And this is interesting.

30
00:01:45,600 --> 00:01:46,760
 So listen to this.

31
00:01:46,760 --> 00:01:51,720
 In many plans, both partners must be covered to activate maternity benefits.

32
00:01:51,720 --> 00:01:53,360
 Next is the high premium.

33
00:01:53,360 --> 00:01:54,560
 These plans cost more.

34
00:01:54,560 --> 00:01:58,080
 And if maternity is an add on, check if it can be removed later.

35
00:01:58,080 --> 00:02:01,480
 So the question is, should you even buy a maternity plan?

36
00:02:01,480 --> 00:02:02,480
 Not always.

37
00:02:02,480 --> 00:02:06,880
 First check, do you or your spouse already have corporate insurance because most corporate

38
00:02:06,880 --> 00:02:09,880
 health policies offer better maternity benefits.

39
00:02:09,880 --> 00:02:13,240
 They have shorter or zero waiting periods in most policies.

40
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:15,000
 They don't charge extra.

41
00:02:15,000 --> 00:02:20,000
 In fact, if either partner has a corporate plan, that should be your first option.

42
00:02:20,040 --> 00:02:24,520
 But if you're planning ahead and don't have corporate cover, then yes, buying a personal

43
00:02:24,520 --> 00:02:27,680
 policy with maternity benefits may make early sense.

44
00:02:27,680 --> 00:02:30,760
 But here are some things to check before you buy.

45
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:32,160
 What is the waiting period?

46
00:02:32,160 --> 00:02:33,860
 What's the sublimit on maternity?

47
00:02:33,860 --> 00:02:36,560
 Is IVF or surrogacy covered if needed?

48
00:02:36,560 --> 00:02:38,000
 What's covered for the baby?

49
00:02:38,000 --> 00:02:39,000
 Vaccinations?

50
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,000
 NICU?

51
00:02:40,000 --> 00:02:42,260
 Can you remove the add on after the baby is born?

52
00:02:42,260 --> 00:02:44,920
 Because you don't want to keep paying the extra premium.

53
00:02:44,920 --> 00:02:49,960
 And remember, vitamins, supplements, voluntary terminations and cosmetic procedures are not

54
00:02:50,000 --> 00:02:51,000
 covered.

55
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:55,760
 Ectopic pregnancy is usually covered under the base health plan, not maternity.

56
